21/03/2005
DOHA, Qatar -- Macedonia and Qatar have agreed to boost bilateral relations, particularly economic co-operation.
Macedonian Foreign Minister Ilinka Mitreva, on a weekend visit to Qatar, met with state leader Amir Hamad bin Khalifa Al Thani and urged companies in both countries to intensify contacts.
At The Hague, meanwhile, former Macedonian security official Johan Tarculovski made his first appearance before the UN war crimes tribunal on Monday.
He was allowed to delay entering his plea by one month.
He and former Interior Minister Ljube Boskovski are accused of crimes committed during the 2001 interethnic conflict.
(Macedonian government Web site, A1 TV, Makfax - 21/03/05;
Monitor - 20/03/05;
Makfax - 19/03/05)
